  "text": "To further measure lysosomal TRPML1 activity and lysosomal Ca 2ϩ release in intact cells, we have generated a lysosome-targeted genetically encoded Ca 2ϩ indicator by fusing GECO, a single wavelength genetically encoded Ca 2ϩ indicator [CITATION_1] , to the cytoplasmic amino terminus of TRPML1 [CITATION_2] . GECO-TRPML1 has been used as a probe to specifically measure TRPML1-mediated lysosomal Ca 2ϩ release, representing TRPML1 activity [CITATION_3] . To exclude the possible contamination of external Ca 2ϩ , low external Ca 2ϩ (nominally free Ca 2ϩ with 1 mM EGTA; free Ca 2ϩ estimated to be Ͻ10 nM) was used for the GECO-TRPML1 fluorescence measurement. As shown in Fig. 3 , E and F, ML-SA1 (10 M)-induced GECO fluorescence intensity in ADA Ϫ/Ϫ cells was significantly smaller than that in WT cells, decreasing from 0.68 Ϯ 0.09 in control fibroblasts to 0.24 Ϯ 0.03 in ADA Ϫ/Ϫ fibroblasts. In contrast, a comparable GPN-induced GECO signal ( Fig. 3G ) and ionomycin-induced GECO signal ( Fig. 3H ) were observed between WT and ADA Ϫ/Ϫ cells. These data suggest that TRPML1 activity is reduced in lysosomes of human skin fibroblasts with ADA deficiency.",
